<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-13T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-13T13:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/15372: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-13T19:00:00+01:00">September
                                    13, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 13—6:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1953. For Hornbeck. Your 884, September 12, 5 p.m.<note n="29" xml:id="d223fn29">Not printed, but see telegram No. 170, September
                                12, 5 p.m., to the Ambassador in China, <ref target="#pg_245">p.
                                    245</ref>.</note> I have not transmitted and will not transmit
                            the message you communicated in your telegram under reference. I have,
                            however, requested Rajchman’s eminent associate in Paris to inform
                            Rajchman that I resent his attempt to use me as a hopper for
                            communications of this sort.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>